  uiType: 0
  text: '2. Concerning fear of the Lord

    

    And before him at the foot of
    the mountain stands an image full of eyes on all sides. For the Fear of the Lord
    stands in God''s presence with humility and gazes on the Kingdom of God, surrounded
    by the clarity of a good and just intention, exercising her zeal and stability
    among humans. And thus you can discern no human form in her on account of those
    eyes. For by the acute sight of her contemplation she counters all forgetfulness
    of God''s justice, which people often feel in their mental tedium, so no inquiry
    by weak mortals eludes her vigilance.'
  image: {fileID: 0}
